<ValidityStateTooLong>
<summary>
The read-only <strong><c>tooLong</c></strong> property of a <strong><see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/ValidityState"><c>ValidityState</c></see></strong> object indicates if the value of an <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input">input</see> or <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/textarea">textarea</see>, after having been edited by the user, exceeds the maximum code-unit length established by the element's <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Attributes/maxlength"><c>maxlength</c></see> attribute.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Constraint_validation">Constraint validation</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Forms/Form_validation">Forms: Data form validation</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/ValidityState/tooLong"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
</ValidityStateTooLong>
